claims:
Claims Claims 1 . A pneumatic gauge and pressure control device comprising a pneumatic gauge that is manually movable from a neutral position to either: (i) a fill position in which the pneumatic gauge and pressure control device causes compressed air to be communicated from an associated compressed air source into an associated device or system; (ii) a vent position in which the pneumatic gauge and pressure control device causes compressed air to be vented from the associated device or system. 2. The pneumatic gauge and pressure control device as set forth in claim 1 , wherein said pneumatic gauge is one of: (i) rotatable about an axis from the neutral position to the fill position and the vent position; (ii) is slidable along an axis from the neutral position to the fill position and the vent position. 3. The pneumatic gauge and pressure control device as set forth in claim 1 or claim 2, wherein said device provides a path for compressed air to flow from the associated compressed air source to the associated device or system when the pneumatic gauge is located in the fill position. 4. The pneumatic gauge and pressure control device as set forth in any of claims 1 - 3, wherein said device provides a path for compressed air to flow from the associated device or system to a vent when the pneumatic gauge is located in the vent position. 5. The pneumatic gauge and pressure control device as set forth in any of claims 1 - 4, wherein said device comprises at least one electrical switch that provides an electrical output that controls at least one valve, wherein, in response to said electrical output, said at least one valve: (i) allows flow of compressed air from the associated compressed air source to the associated device or system through said at least one valve when the pneumatic gauge is located in the fill position; (ii) allows flow of compressed air from the associated device or system to the vent through said at least one valve when the pneumatic gauge is located in the vent position; (iii) blocks flow of compressed air into or out of the associated device or system when the pneumatic gauge is located in the neutral position. 6. The pneumatic gauge and pressure control device as set forth in any of claims 1 - 5, wherein said device provides an electrical output that causes an associated air compressor of the associated compressed air source of compressed air to be energized when the pneumatic gauge is located in the fill position. 7. The pneumatic gauge and pressure control device as set forth in claim 6, wherein the associated air compressor is directly or indirectly in fluid communication with the associated device or system and is adapted to supply compressed air to the associated device or system directly and/or through the pneumatic gauge and pressure control device when the associated air compressor is energized when said pneumatic gauge is located in the fill position. 8. The pneumatic gauge and pressure control device as set forth in any of claims 1 - 7, wherein the fill position and the vent position are obtained respectively by rotating the pneumatic gauge in first and second angular directions from the neutral position or are obtained respectively by rotating the pneumatic gauge in a single angular direction by first and second different angular distances from the neutral position. 9. The pneumatic gauge and pressure control device as set forth in any of claims 1 - 8, comprising: a first body comprising an air inlet passage adapted to be connected to the associated compressed air source and a primary air outlet passage; a second body that moves relative to the first body from a first operative position to a second operative position, wherein said pneumatic gauge is operably connected to said second body to move together with said second body, said second body comprising a distribution orifice; a main airflow passage that fluidical ly connects said primary air outlet passage to said pneumatic gauge; a branch distribution passage that fluidically connects said main airflow passage to said distribution orifice of said second body; 

 wherein said second body is located in said second operative position in which the distribution orifice is in fluid communication with said air inlet passage of said first body when said pneumatic gauge is moved to the fill position such that said primary air outlet passage of said first body is also in fluid communication with said air inlet passage of said first body through said main airflow passage and said branch distribution passage when said pneumatic gauge is moved to the fill position. 10. The pneumatic gauge and pressure control device as set forth in claim 9, wherein said first body further comprises a vent passage that communicates with an ambient atmosphere external to said first body, and wherein said second body is located in a third operative position in which said distribution orifice is in fluid communication with said vent passage of said first body when said pneumatic gauge is moved to the vent position such that said primary air outlet passage of said first body is also in fluid communication with said vent passage of said first body through said main airflow passage and said branch distribution passage when said pneumatic gauge is moved to the vent position. 11. The pneumatic gauge and pressure control device as set forth in claim 10, wherein said first body further comprises an airflow stop, and wherein said second body is located in said first operative position in which the distribution orifice is in fluid communication with said airflow stop of said first body when said pneumatic gauge is moved to the neutral position such that said airflow stop blocks airflow into or out of said distribution orifice when said pneumatic gauge is moved to the neutral position. 12. The pneumatic gauge and pressure control device as set forth in any of claims claim 9 to 11 , wherein said second body is rotatably connected to said first body for rotation about said axis such that said pneumatic gauge and said second body rotate relative to said first body about said axis when said pneumatic gauge is moved said fill position and said vent position. 13. The pneumatic gauge and pressure control device as set forth in any of claims 1 - 12 further including a spring that resiliently biases the pneumatic gauge: (i) from the fill position toward the neutral position; and (ii) from the vent position toward the neutral position. 14. The pneumatic gauge and pressure control device as set forth in any of claims 1 - 13, wherein said main airflow passage and said branch distribution passage are provided in a main fitting, and wherein said main fitting non-rotatably connects said pneumatic gauge to said second body such that said pneumatic gauge and said second body rotate as a unit about said axis. 15. The pneumatic gauge and pressure control device as set forth in claim 14, wherein said main fitting comprises: a main portion including said main airflow passage; a branch portion that comprises said branch distribution passage, wherein said branch portion includes an outer end that is radially offset from said axis; and a torque input portion that is radially offset from said axis; wherein said toque input portion is operably coupled to rotate about said axis with said pneumatic gauge and said outer end of said branch portion is operably engaged with said second body to rotate with said second body about said axis. 16. The pneumatic gauge and pressure control device as set forth in claim 15, wherein said pneumatic gauge is non-rotatably engaged with a gauge plate such that said pneumatic gauge and gauge plate rotate as a unit about said axis, said gauge plate comprises a torque output portion that is operably engaged with said torque input portion of said main fitting to operably couple the pneumatic gauge to the main fitting. 17. The pneumatic gauge and pressure control device as set forth in any of the preceding claims 9 - 16, further comprising external threads on said first body adapted to be engaged by a mounting nut to secure the first body to an associated panel or other associated mounting structure. 18. The pneumatic gauge and pressure control device as set forth in claim 17, further comprising a bezel engaged with the external threads of the first body, wherein said bezel axially captures said second body to said first body. 19. The pneumatic gauge and pressure control device as set forth in any of preceding claims 9 - 18, wherein said first body comprises a cup-like structure including 

an annular wall that defines a main bore, said first body comprising an inner end wall that extends across and at least partially closes an inner end of the main bore, wherein the air inlet passage and the primary air outlet passage are located in said inner end wall. 20. A pneumatic system including a pneumatic gauge and pressure control device as set forth in any of claims 1 - 19. 21 . The pneumatic system as set forth in claim 20 further including a compressed air source comprising at least one of an air tank and an air compressor. 22. The pneumatic system as set forth in claim 21 , comprising at least one of a vehicle tire and vehicle air spring that receives compressed air from the compressed air source when the pneumatic gauge of the device is located in the fill position. 23. A method for adding or removing compressed air from a pneumatic system, said method comprising: manually moving a pneumatic pressure gauge from a neutral position to a fill position to cause compressed air to be communicated from an associated compressed air source into the pneumatic system; and, manually moving the pneumatic gauge from the neutral position or from the fill position to a vent position to cause compressed air to be vented from the pneumatic system. 24. The method as set forth in claim 23, wherein said steps of manually moving the pneumatic pressure gauge comprise rotating the pneumatic pressure gauge about an axis of rotation.
